'''Hathol''' (born {{FA|365}}) was an [[Edain|Adan]], belonging to the tribes of [[Men]] who crossed the [[Blue Mountains]] from the eastern lands. He was the grandson of [[Malach|Malach Aradan]].<ref name=hador>{{WJ|West}}, ''Commentary, (ii) House of Hador'', p. 234</ref>

==Etymology==
In the genealogical tree of the folk of Marach, ''Hathol'' is translated as "the Axe",<ref name=hador /> the [[Sindarin]] form of the old [[Noldorin]] ''Hathel''.<ref>{{LR|Etymologies}}, entry "SYAD"</ref>

